    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"50 kilogram\"><math alttext=\"50 kilogram\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>50</mn><mtext>-kg</mtext></math></span></span> student sitting in a rolling chair at rest pushes against a wall, which applies a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 newton second\"><math alttext=\"10 newton second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>N·s</mtext></math></span></span> horizontal impulse to the student. Later, a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"40 kilogram\"><math alttext=\"40 kilogram\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>40</mn><mtext>-kg</mtext></math></span></span> student is at rest in the same rolling chair and catches a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 kilogram\"><math alttext=\"10 kilogram\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mtext>-kg</mtext></math></span></span> ball while applying a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 newton second\"><math alttext=\"10 newton second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>N·s</mtext></math></span></span> horizontal impulse to the ball. Which of the following statements best describes the students’ final speeds and provides valid reasoning supporting the claim?</p>\n",
